# ===========================================
# Stock Dashboard Environment Configuration
# ===========================================

# REQUIRED ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# These variables must be set for the application to work properly

# Supabase Configuration (REQUIRED)
# Get your Supabase config from: https://app.supabase.com/
# 1. Create a new project or use existing one
# 2. Go to Settings > API to find your URL and anon key
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# ===========================================
# OPTIONAL ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# These variables have defaults but can be customized

# News API Configuration (OPTIONAL)
# Get your free API key from https://newsapi.org/
# Free tier: 500 requests per day
# Note: News features will be disabled without this key
VITE_NEWS_API_KEY=your_news_api_key_here
VITE_NEWS_API_BASE_URL=https://newsapi.org/v2

# ===========================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ===========================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env in the root directory
# 2. Replace placeholder values with your actual API keys
# 3. Ensure .env is listed in your .gitignore file
# 4. Restart your development server after making changes
#
# For production deployment:
# - Set these variables in your hosting platform's environment settings
# - Never commit real API keys to version control
# - Use different API keys for development and production